# Python Project Guidelines

This file defines coding standards and best practices for Python projects

## Code Style and Documentation
- All code, comments, docstrings, and string literals must be in English
- Follow Google Python Style Guide (https://google.github.io/styleguide/pyguide.html)
- Use type hints for function parameters and return values
- Maximum line length: 88 characters (Black formatter default)
- Use meaningful variable and function names that reflect their purpose
- Write docstrings for all modules, classes, and functions using Google style
- Comments should start with a capital letter and should not end with a period
- Complete sentences in docstrings should end with a period
